          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691579730559-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>to a small bowl with the<strong> rice vinegar</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span>of the <strong>cornflour</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and mix it all together</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong> <strong>base</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691579733702-x200.jpg",
